  <h2>Veteran Health Accommodations</h2>

  <article class="command-card">
    <header>
      <h3>Bad Health Days Protocol</h3>
      <span class="difficulty-badge medium">Adaptive Training</span>
    </header>

    <details open>
      <summary><strong>High Pain/PTSD Symptom Days</strong></summary>
      <h4>Minimum Training (5-10 minutes total):</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Focus on easiest, most reliable commands</li>
        <li>Heavy rewards - make it fun and easy</li>
        <li>Don't introduce anything new</li>
        <li>Seated training options</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Modified Exercise:</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Shorter walks (even just to driveway)</li>
        <li>Drive to easy location</li>
        <li>Consider hiring dog walker</li>
        <li>Mental enrichment substitutes (Kong, puzzle toys)</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>No Guilt Rule:</h4>
      <p>Recovery days are part of training. Rest helps both you and Gypsy process learning and heal.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary><strong>Energy Management Tips</strong></summary>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Train During Peak Energy:</strong> Schedule main session when you're sharpest</li>
        <li><strong>Batch Activities:</strong> Walk + training + bathroom = one trip</li>
        <li><strong>Seated Training:</strong> Most exercises work from a chair</li>
        <li><strong>Use Daily Life:</strong> Sit before doors, down-stay while cooking</li>
      </ol>
    </details>
  </article>

