  <h2>Rest & Recovery</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary><strong>Why Rest Matters</strong></summary>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Memory Consolidation:</strong> Learning solidifies during sleep</li>
      <li><strong>Prevent Burnout:</strong> Too much training creates stress</li>
      <li><strong>Physical Recovery:</strong> Growing dogs need rest</li>
      <li><strong>Behavioral Balance:</strong> Overtrained dogs become anxious</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Mandatory Rest:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>One full day per week - no formal training</li>
      <li>After intense sessions (first public access, new tasks)</li>
      <li>Active rest: decompression walks, play, bonding time</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

